A number of non-governmental organisations allege that chemical weapons were recently used in the Syrian rebel-controlled town of Douma, in eastern Ghouma. 

Meanwhile, there are growing calls for international investigators including the International Committee of the Red Cross (ICRC) to be allowed to enter Douma to investigate the alleged chemical attack. 

At this point the ICRC says it has no information on the reported incident, but to reflect on the ban on chemical weapons in general, here's the organisation's Jason Straziuso...

